From: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Dec 2024 22:00:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 016/314] UPSTREAM: arm64: defconfig: Enable Rockchip
 extensions for Synopsys DW HDMI QP

Enable Rockchip specific extensions for Synopsys DesignWare HDMI
Quad-Pixel (QP) driver.  This is needed to provide HDMI output support
for the boards based on RK3588 SoC.

Signed-off-by: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20241202-dw-hdmi-qp-rk-defconfig-v1-1-38757fc053d0@collabora.com
Signed-off-by: Heiko Stuebner <heiko@sntech.de>

(cherry picked from commit 06835ccec2efb71d54a810265e8ef69b1011608e)
Signed-off-by: Kexy Biscuit <kexybiscuit@aosc.io>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/defconfig b/arch/arm64/configs/defconfig
index c6d6a31a8f48..7e3fbe6ccaab 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/defconfig
@@ -872,6 +872,7 @@ CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_VOP2=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_ANALOGIX_DP=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_CDN_DP=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_DW_HDMI=y
+CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_DW_HDMI_QP=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_DW_MIPI_DSI=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_INNO_HDMI=y
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_LVDS=y
